  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local Cooperation Fund (LCF) in Egypt</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A group of lawyers in the target area interested in women issues will be provided with legal skills and necessary knowledge to handle cases of violence against women before national courts to provide victims of violence of women with direct legal support. After the completion of the training courses for lawyers, a hotline will be launched in the target area to receive complaints from oppressed women to provide them with legal consultation and direct legal support if necessary.It is proposed also to create Support Groups (SGs) consisting of positive examples of women who have had experiences of violence and as well as others of who underwent serious experiences of violence.Series of seminars will be held to address problems and consequences of violence against women. The seminars will target women of the project beneficiaries and other turnouts form the target area.</narrative>
  </description>
